Frequently Asked Questions for StealthGas (NASDAQ:GASS)
What is StealthGas' stock symbol?

StealthGas trades on the NASDAQ under the ticker symbol "GASS."



How were StealthGas' earnings last quarter?

StealthGas, Inc. (NASDAQ:GASS) posted its earnings results on Thursday, May, 25th. The company reported $0.05 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Zacks' consensus estimate of ($0.02) by $0.07. The company had revenue of $38.06 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $33.30 million. StealthGas had a negative net margin of 4.41% and a negative return on equity of 0.09%.  View StealthGas' Earnings History.



When will StealthGas make its next earnings announcement?

StealthGas is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Wednesday, August, 23rd 2017. View Earnings Estimates for StealthGas.



Where is StealthGas' stock going? Where will StealthGas' stock price be in 2017?

2 equities research analysts have issued 1-year target prices for StealthGas' stock. Their predictions range from $4.00 to $7.00. On average, they expect StealthGas' share price to reach $5.50 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for StealthGas.



Who are some of StealthGas' key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to StealthGas include Navios Maritime Midstream Partners LP (NAP), Danaos Corporation (DAC), Navios Maritime Acquisition Corporation (NNA), Freightcar America (RAIL), Overseas Shipholding Group (OSG), Aegean Marine Petroleum Network (ANW), Era Group (ERA), CryoPort (CYRX), Navios Maritime Holdings (NM), Celadon Group (CGI), P.A.M. Transportation Services (PTSI), Pangaea Logistics Solutions (PANL), USA Truck (USAK), Global Ship Lease (GSL), Tidewater (TDW), Odyssey Marine Exploration (OMEX), Nordic American Offshore Ltd (NAO) and Euroseas (ESEA).



Who are StealthGas' key executives?

StealthGas' management team includes the folowing people: Michael Gordon Jolliffe, Independent Chairman of the BoardHarry N. Vafias, President, Chief Executive Officer, Interim Chief Financial Officer, DirectorLambros Babilis, Executive Deputy Chairman of the BoardDiamantis Andriotis, Chief Technical OfficerMarkos Drakos, Independent DirectorJohn Kostoyannis, Independent Director



Who owns StealthGas stock?

StealthGas' stock is owned by a number of of retail and institutional investors. Top institutional investors include Russell Investments Group Ltd. (1.36%), Gagnon Securities LLC (0.39%) and Creative Planning (0.10%).  View Institutional Ownership Trends for StealthGas.



Who bought StealthGas stock? Who is buying StealthGas stock?

StealthGas' stock was acquired by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Russell Investments Group Ltd. and Gagnon Securities LLC.  View Insider Buying and Selling for StealthGas.



How do I buy StealthGas stock? 

Shares of StealthGas can be purchased through any online brokerage account. Popular online brokerages include Vanguard Brokerage Services, TD Ameritrade, E*TRADE, Scottrade, Fidelity and Charles Schwab. 



What is StealthGas' stock price today?

One share of StealthGas stock can currently be purchased for approximately $2.94.


